article.headline: S. Dakota St. 61, N. Iowa 55
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- South Dakota State trailed by four points at halftime but rallied in the second half Friday to hand Northern Iowa its first loss of the season 61-55. NIU (4-1) shot 46 percent in the first half to take a 31-27 lead. But the Panthers made only one of six 3-pointers in the second half and shot 33 percent after the break. The Jackrabbits (2-2) took advantage of the opportunity. They shot 47 percent in the second half and enjoyed a big free throw advantage. They were 14-for-18 from the free throw line in the second half and made 18 of 23 free throws in the game. The Panthers were just 9-for-11. Garrett Callahan led SDSU with 16 points and four assists. Kai Williams added 13 points and eight rebounds. The Panthers outrebounded SDSU 35-23. Jordan Eglaeder had 18 points and 14 rebounds. Adam Koch and Jared Josten chipeed in 10 points apiece.
